<a href="#0" id="0">Our central idea for new sentiment word detection is as follows.</a>
<a href="#1" id="1">Starting from very few seed words (for example, just one seed word), we can extract lexical patterns that have strong statistical association with the seed words; the extracted lexical patterns can be further used in finding more new words, and the most probable new words can be added into the seed word set for the next iteration; and the process can be run iteratively until a stop condition is met.</a>
<a href="#2" id="2">The key issues are to measure the utility of a pattern and to quantify the possibility of a word being a new word.</a>
